item.title: Jupiter with brown ovals. 10/1/21.
item.description: Jupiter. Taken 10/1/21 with Canon T5i on the Celestron 11" with eyepiece projection. Stacked image from video. Brown ovals are visible above the N. equatorial belt. The Great Red Spot is visible below the S. Equatorial belt. Image was flipped for correct orientation (the S. Eq. Belt is darker on the right side of the GRS.)
item.media:description: Jupiter. Taken 10/1/21 with Canon T5i on the Celestron 11" with eyepiece projection. Stacked image from video. Brown ovals are visible above the N. equatorial belt. The Great Red Spot is visible below the S. Equatorial belt. Image was flipped for correct orientation (the S. Eq. Belt is darker on the right side of the GRS.)
